@node History "So how many versions of TeaBot ? :)"

History :


Version 0.96 First Aminet release. 
(05-02-98)

Version 0.96a/b  Removed DCC chat launch of FServ, whoops it doesn't work ! :)
(06-02-98)

Version 0.96c  Added pointer for FServ: to a Env varible, to save people doing assigns =)
(07-02-98)     TeaBot pops up a requester if Fserv assign isn't there. Use ^FservAssign to
               Change the assign after its already set (localy only).

Version 0.96d  Rewrote level code, now requires the user to be on channel or
(19-02-98)     a user supplied usermask, should be _MUCH_ safer :)
               Added Error messages to FServassign and help messages to FServ/FServassign.
               Made TeaBot see more invalid CTCP messages (Just for fun).
               Made TeaBots DCC resume work with different setups (I hope).

Version 0.96e  Added Basic OPS protection to TeaBot, Default setting is OFF, can be toggled on/off
(20-02-98)     with ^OpsProtect command. Hows it works, ok if a op with a level less than 4
               deops another Op (any level) Teabot Reops the op and deops the -4 op :)
               Is that clear I think not :^)

Version 0.96f  Fixed problem with FServ and AmIRC 2.0x (it didn't work), Added Auto 
(28-03-98)     UserDatabase at last (every five minutes it writes the userdatabase back to HD).             
               Hangman now allows any word eg ^hangr MrQue MyNewWord 
               (idea by Philip Goddard, thanks :)) Changed Tryme a little, some of the 
               code cleaned up a bit. Explained in Guide how to Add Faq's @{"offline" LINK Offline} (also PG).
               Amirc doesn't like RAW joins/Parts changed to /Says.
               ===REMEMBER TO REPLACE YOUR FSERV.AMIRX even if you don't use Amirc 2.0x===

Version 0.97   Added Mass change Level to 1 command, use with care, changes the WHOLE of the database
(02-04-98)     (It leaves your hostmask at current level). Changed the welcome to TeaBot message.
               Loads of Cosmetic changes and code optimizations. Fixed the creation of the 
               Faqlist. TeaBot will notify you (If your local to TeaBot) when FServ is connected 
               to or Hangman is setup or a user is added to the database or a level is changed
               (You are Private messaged a notice) :)  Combined FServ into Teabot. Teabot 
               will launch FServ if it gets a ctcp XDCC. Fixed some stuff that I should 
               had done ages ago (too lazy ;)). Fixed a problem (I hope) with Auto database 
               backup not working after midnight. Fixed some stuff in ^Part.  

Version 0.97a Fixed (I hope) join message on startup. And other small stuff.
(12-05-98)

Version 0.97b  FServ can now be disabled with new ^FServAccess command, toggles on/off.
(20-05-98)     Database files are auto-updated, On first run of this new version TeaBot sets
               Fserv to OFF. Updated Guide a bit :)

Version 0.97c  Ever wanted to know if opsprotection or fserv was on/off ^status commands
(14-07-98)     will tell you :)  FServ can now only be launched once per user (will save
               of cpu time etc.). Fserv now only auto quits if no dcc sends are active
               (sending) to current user. More code cleaned up. Fixed typos in this readme ;)
               Updated the guide file.


Version 0.97d Added Tell command.
(08-08-98)    *Special beta-tester birthday edition ;)*
              (btw this was ickle Dave, btw wheres my betatester gone  ;))


New release:
Version 0.97e Fixed (I hope) a slight problem with Tell (Sometimes Teabot wouldn't notify people
(26-10-98)    that they had messages waiting). Removed some code that seemed to be included
              twice ;)  Made join message (even) more reliable. Made TeaBot check for commands
              after it adds a newuser to the database. Made DCC Chat launch FServ.


Version 0.98
(10-12-98)

Added		 G_eneral M_essage J_oin greet command (GMJ), any user that
        	 joins gets a greet, btw is can be turned off (Off has default).
		 Turn it on with ^GMJ and to check its on use ^Status,
                 
                 To set GMJ use ^SetGMJ [Message]
                 eg, ^SetGMJ Welcome to my channel !
                 (Thanks to Barbarian L. Bohl for that idea :))
              
Overworked	 More code cleaned up a little. 


Fixed            Viewgreet looking up blank nicknames. (Thanks to Mohammad Asiri for the bug
                 report !)


Added            Kiss command (requested by Mohammad Asiri)



Version 0.98ß
(22-05-99)


Well well well :-) After a long long while I finally
upload a sortof beta on TeaBot 0.98, please test the
features there may be bugs in the datafile handling.
Well I lost the new upto date source and it took me ages
to update the old one I had got, anyway have fun and email
me if it screws up, with a bit of luck I'll add new 
features again so email and pester me NOW ! =)


New release:
Version 0.98.1
(28-07-99)


Added the missing commands to the showcomands list.
Fixed a little bug added in 0.98ßeta where Teabot didn't ever do 'Unknown command'.
Fixed Slight bug in the way TeaBot echos text with hostmask level changes
Added Opition to change the Bot command (the ^) to any one character :)
Made TeaBot check if people are on the channel before trying to op or deop them.
Updated the Status command to show info on new commands.
I'm now happy with the state of Teabot so I've dropped its ßeta status :-)
Added Fun command called Cookie 8)

@{b}Version 0.98.2@{ub}
@{b}(11-08-99)@{ub}

A little installation for you in this one, copy the storydb file to s:
thats your lot 8)  You can edit by hand the file to change it around to 
your liking, just read the information inside the file to help you out..
They new command is called Story where teaBot makes up storys about the people
on the channel 8)
Right now why I uploaded a very small upgrade well because over the last
few years Amiga software is basicly getting so few and far between that I
desided to get a pc, the days of downloading quality amiga software 
all the time is over (please prove me wrong !) so for the likes of PC 
software I'm moving there....... this DOESN'T mean the end of TeaBot 
perhaps just a little pause while I get both or one machine up and running... 8)

TeaBot will return in version 0.98.3, perhaps under emulation tho...


@{" Back to Index " LINK Main}

<>< a ickle fishy.
